1315
01:30:24.185 --> 01:30:25.812
It's kind of sick.

1316
01:30:27.455 --> 01:30:29.651
You act like a vampire.

1317
01:30:30.124 --> 01:30:33.651
You suck people's blood
and use it to make money.


1318
01:30:33.861 --> 01:30:36.489
You confuse everything.
It's tiring.


1319
01:30:37.098 --> 01:30:37.894
Let's stop.

1320
01:30:39.934 --> 01:30:41.424
You bet we'll stop.

1321
01:30:52.680 --> 01:30:55.206
It isn't always easy.

1322
01:30:55.449 --> 01:30:59.386
In a group,
you always have conflicting ideas.


1323
01:30:59.554 --> 01:31:02.023
I get pissed off sometimes,

1324
01:31:02.223 --> 01:31:04.021
but in the long run,

1325
01:31:04.225 --> 01:31:07.991
I've met people I'd never have met
in real life.


1326
01:31:09.130 --> 01:31:12.100
We work hard. It's no holiday.

1327
01:31:12.300 --> 01:31:14.894
We'll try to make something good.

1328
01:31:16.637 --> 01:31:20.164
I knew we wouldn't write a best-seller.

1329
01:31:20.841 --> 01:31:24.106
But it's better than mixing cement

1330
01:31:24.312 --> 01:31:25.677
or laying cables.

1331
01:31:26.047 --> 01:31:28.573
It's fun, we're having a laugh.

1332
01:31:30.351 --> 01:31:31.546
It's cool.

1333
01:31:33.487 --> 01:31:36.184
Writing a novel, quite frankly...

1334
01:31:37.158 --> 01:31:39.126
I never thought I would.

1335
01:31:40.261 --> 01:31:43.458
It's a totally awesome experience.

1336
01:31:44.265 --> 01:31:45.892
On my CV,

1337
01:31:46.100 --> 01:31:48.626
it'll look really good.

1338
01:31:50.504 --> 01:31:54.668
Before this, I wrote a lot,
so it's an opportunity


1339
01:31:54.875 --> 01:31:57.242
in relation to my future career

1340
01:31:57.445 --> 01:32:00.278
as a writer or just a journalist.

1341
01:32:00.514 --> 01:32:02.539
In any case, we talk a lot.

1342
01:32:03.217 --> 01:32:06.812
I've discovered ways of thinking
I never suspected.


1343
01:32:07.021 --> 01:32:08.955
Who are these youngsters?

1344
01:32:09.123 --> 01:32:11.820
It's a social integration course, right'?

1345
01:32:12.627 --> 01:32:14.618
They're like other youngsters

1346
01:32:14.862 --> 01:32:17.797
who didn't get much out of school

1347
01:32:17.965 --> 01:32:19.899
or culture either.

1348
01:32:20.101 --> 01:32:21.091
<i>I'm sorry. hope</i>

1349
01:32:21.302 --> 01:32:25.671
they'll discover a relationship
with tree and personal writing


1350
01:32:25.906 --> 01:32:27.340
to reconcile them with literature

1351
01:32:28.275 --> 01:32:29.572
and the world.

1352
01:32:29.777 --> 01:32:31.302
Ambitious, isn't it?

1353
01:32:31.545 --> 01:32:33.377
We need to remember

1354
01:32:33.581 --> 01:32:36.278
that the goal is to write a thriller.

1355
01:32:37.051 --> 01:32:40.715
hurt destined to be published.

1356
01:32:40.921 --> 01:32:42.047
Yes, absolutely.

1357
01:32:42.256 --> 01:32:44.281
It will be,
and that's important.


1358
01:32:44.492 --> 01:32:47.325
There's nothing more stimulating

1359
01:32:47.561 --> 01:32:49.655
than creating a work,

1360
01:32:50.131 --> 01:32:52.156
whatever its literary value.

1361
01:32:52.400 --> 01:32:55.893
We're not writing for nothing
or for fun.


1362
01:32:56.103 --> 01:32:57.400
There's a result.

1363
01:32:57.605 --> 01:32:59.369
The most interesting thing

1364
01:32:59.573 --> 01:33:02.873
is to see them change over time.

1365
01:33:03.077 --> 01:33:05.671
The way they view themselves alters.

1366
01:33:06.580 --> 01:33:09.379
Writing is a good way to shake yourself,

1367
01:33:09.583 --> 01:33:12.883
escape idleness
and gain in confidence.


1368
01:33:13.487 --> 01:33:14.852
The novel is a pretext,

1369
01:33:15.456 --> 01:33:17.083
the means to do that.

1370
01:34:48.616 --> 01:34:50.141
What are you doing here?

1371
01:35:24.084 --> 01:35:25.779
What's that gun'?

1372
01:35:26.887 --> 01:35:28.355
Are you crazy?

1373
01:35:29.456 --> 01:35:30.582
I'm OK.

1374
01:35:52.446 --> 01:35:53.914
I don't understand.

1375
01:35:55.950 --> 01:35:57.941
What do you want me to say?

1376
01:35:58.853 --> 01:36:00.787
What do you want me to do'?

1377
01:36:01.655 --> 01:36:03.145
What can I do'?

1378
01:36:05.993 --> 01:36:07.290
Can I help you?

1379
01:36:08.829 --> 01:36:10.263
I don't need help.

1380
01:36:19.807 --> 01:36:21.901
So put the gun down, please.

1381
01:36:23.043 --> 01:36:23.908
No.

1382
01:36:26.814 --> 01:36:28.908
Stop pointing it at me at least.

1383
01:36:46.033 --> 01:36:48.161
I'm getting really scared.

1384
01:37:03.150 --> 01:37:04.640
We'll go fora ride.

1385
01:37:06.353 --> 01:37:09.015
In your car.
I'll tell you where to go.


1386
01:37:48.595 --> 01:37:50.222
Let's talk, Antoine.

1387
01:37:52.032 --> 01:37:53.727
Explain everything.

1388
01:37:56.637 --> 01:37:58.071
Do you trust me?

1389
01:38:00.274 --> 01:38:02.641
You know you can trust me-.

1390
01:38:03.944 --> 01:38:05.139
Right, Antoine?

1391
01:38:08.415 --> 01:38:09.940
I won't tell anyone.

1392
01:38:20.060 --> 01:38:22.085
Maybe we misunderstood each other.

1393
01:38:23.897 --> 01:38:25.763
Maybe you can explain.

1394
01:38:33.173 --> 01:38:35.267
Take that track on the left.

1395
01:38:53.360 --> 01:38:54.850
Where are we going?

1396
01:39:05.105 --> 01:39:06.470
Stop here.

1397
01:39:07.674 --> 01:39:09.164
We'll walk from here.

1398
01:39:18.519 --> 01:39:19.884
What do you want?

1399
01:39:20.888 --> 01:39:22.413
I don't wanna talk.

1400
01:41:04.258 --> 01:41:05.419
It's weird.

1401
01:41:06.160 --> 01:41:07.924
I'd never been at night.

1402
01:41:25.679 --> 01:41:26.840
Are you cold?

1403
01:41:28.248 --> 01:41:29.215
No.

1404
01:42:35.549 --> 01:42:36.983
Go if you want.

1405
01:45:18.345 --> 01:45:20.279
- Olivia?
- Yes?


1406
01:45:20.480 --> 01:45:23.472
Do you have a synonym for "bury“?

1407
01:45:24.518 --> 01:45:25.679
Inter.

1408
01:45:26.153 --> 01:45:28.019
Lay to rest, entomb...

1409
01:45:28.221 --> 01:45:30.690
Inter is good.

1410
01:45:50.043 --> 01:45:51.374
Look who's back!

1411
01:45:53.246 --> 01:45:54.236
Hello.

1412
01:45:59.953 --> 01:46:02.115
I want to read something I wrote.

1413
01:46:03.190 --> 01:46:05.488
It's to say goodbye for good.

1414
01:46:05.926 --> 01:46:07.860
Why did you piss us off?

1415
01:46:08.695 --> 01:46:10.220
We don't give a shit.

1416
01:46:10.430 --> 01:46:13.365
- Looking for applause'?
- He drifts in and out.


1417
01:46:14.468 --> 01:46:17.062
I thought about sending it,

1418
01:46:18.104 --> 01:46:20.300
but I preferred to read it here.

1419
01:46:20.907 --> 01:46:22.432
I don't know now.

1420
01:46:24.811 --> 01:46:26.176
It's not too long?

1421
01:46:29.149 --> 01:46:30.810
Go on, we're listening.

1422
01:46:40.093 --> 01:46:41.117
"Yes...

1423
01:46:41.561 --> 01:46:44.929
A man can kill out of boredom,
just to see.


1424
01:46:45.265 --> 01:46:48.565
He could have shot someone
out of boredom,


1425
01:46:48.768 --> 01:46:51.066
just for something to happen.

1426
01:46:51.304 --> 01:46:52.794
He'd have told the cops

1427
01:46:53.006 --> 01:46:56.840
he shot the guy
for being an Arab or a Jew or gay.


1428
01:46:57.477 --> 01:46:59.172
They'd have understood.

1429
01:46:59.412 --> 01:47:01.039
No explaining to do.

1430
01:47:01.781 --> 01:47:04.716
But the victim didn't matter.

1431
01:47:05.185 --> 01:47:07.620
He could even have shot himself.

1432
01:47:07.821 --> 01:47:09.653
They'd have understood too.

1433
01:47:09.856 --> 01:47:12.951
They'd have said
he had no future, no friends...


1434
01:47:13.159 --> 01:47:14.957
But he did neither one.

1435
01:47:15.161 --> 01:47:16.754
He was too weak.

1436
01:47:17.197 --> 01:47:18.687
He had done nothing.

1437
01:47:21.134 --> 01:47:23.125
So he got bored and waited.

1438
01:47:23.537 --> 01:47:24.902
But for what?

1439
01:47:25.438 --> 01:47:26.701
He drifted along.

1440
01:47:27.474 --> 01:47:29.670
Just to pass the time.

1441
01:47:30.210 --> 01:47:31.871
To kill time, as they say.

1442
01:47:32.112 --> 01:47:34.444
But the town was killing him.

1443
01:47:34.881 --> 01:47:36.713
Always the same routes.

1444
01:47:37.284 --> 01:47:41.482
Sometimes, to dispel his boredom,
he'd take a long detour.


1445
01:47:42.022 --> 01:47:43.512
But it didn't work.

1446
01:47:43.823 --> 01:47:46.622
He knew all the roads and tracks.

1447
01:47:46.893 --> 01:47:50.352
He had travelled them so often,
alone, always alone.


1448
01:47:50.897 --> 01:47:52.524
Always the same landscape.

1449
01:47:52.732 --> 01:47:54.826
The yard that no one could avoid.

1450
01:47:55.035 --> 01:47:59.131
The crane that was religiously preserved
like a work of art-.


1451
01:48:00.340 --> 01:48:02.365
He didn't share that nostalgia.

1452
01:48:02.576 --> 01:48:04.408
He didn't care about the yard,

1453
01:48:04.644 --> 01:48:07.841
the workers or the tankers built there.

1454
01:48:08.815 --> 01:48:10.476
That wasn't his story.

1455
01:48:11.184 --> 01:48:14.518
He'd meet people he knew
and pretend to be happy.


1456
01:48:14.721 --> 01:48:18.248
He knew everyone,
so tried to avoid them.


1457
01:48:19.259 --> 01:48:21.956
He felt
these people smiling at him,


1458
01:48:22.195 --> 01:48:26.154
who claimed to love or help him,
talked to him like an animal.


1459
01:48:26.700 --> 01:48:28.532
An animal to be trained.

1460
01:48:29.169 --> 01:48:32.161
He had to realize,
that even if he was bored,


1461
01:48:32.372 --> 01:48:34.238
even if his friends were strangers,

1462
01:48:34.441 --> 01:48:37.376
even with no future, no friends, no job,

1463
01:48:37.777 --> 01:48:39.438
he should feel lucky.“

1464
01:48:44.451 --> 01:48:45.577
There.

1465
01:48:50.423 --> 01:48:51.754
I'll leave you.

1466
01:48:55.061 --> 01:48:56.187
Goodbye.

1467
